The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, May 12, 2004  Business Briefs																								 New Delhi, May 11: Nanda brothers Anil and Rajan have once again crossed swords, with the former dubbing as illegal the move by Escorts Group to pledge 16 lakh shares of Escorts Heart Institute and Research Centre (EHIRC) to LIC for mopping up Rs 100 crore. Escorts Limited is virtually making a sale and destroying the purpose and status of EHIRC as a public charitable institution, Anil said.																								 New Delhi, May 11: The IDBI-led consortium will meet foreign lenders on Wednesday in London for taking over their outstanding dues in the troubled Dabhol power project. The meeting assumes importance as foreign lenders may proceed for international arbitration if the talks fail, sources said.																								 Mumbai, May 11: Bombay Dyeing Ltd has posted a higher net profit of Rs 53.5 crore in 2003-04 against Rs 32.31 crore in the previous fiscal. The board has recommended a dividend of Rs 4 per share for the year ended March 31, 2004, the company informed the Bombay Stock Exchange today. 																								 New Delhi, May 11: U. D. Choubey has joined Gail (India) Limited as director (marketing). He will be the first director to head the companys marketing division.																								 New Delhi, May 11: The Telecom Regulatory Authority of India (Trai) is examining the issue of hike in roaming charges by some mobile operators, chairman Pradip Baijal said.																								 New Delhi, May 11: The government said it would examine proposals for simplification of procedures for export-oriented units (EOUs) and special economic zones (SEZs) in a time-bound manner. Additional secretary, ministry of commerce, G. K. Pillai said various proposals relating to infrastructure in the SEZs could be examined.																								 New Delhi, May 11: Delhi High Court has cleared Bharti Group of allegations of fraud in getting the approval and sanction of the scheme of arrangements for the transfer of shareholdings in Skycell Communication Ltd.
